## How to configure a Mashup
#### When you are using Cloud test for SAP Sales and Service Cloud service.
- In the left panel chose the ‘Administrator’ work center. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- From the menu click on ‘Mashup Authoring’.

- Click on ‘New’ button and choose mashup type from the list. URL Mashup means that the mashup will open in a new window / tab. HTML Mashup means that the mashup will be embedded in the current window / tab.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the ‘Port Binding’ field you need to link mashup to a desired section in the SAP Portal. In the ‘Mashup Name’ you can chose a name for your mashup. As Type choose “URL”.The url consists of a cloud instance and an extension “/doxee/frontend/process-frame” In the table ‘Request Parameter’ you need to configure following 4 parameters (use Add Row button):filterValue = ID from a portal section that was linked to the mashup (in our case we have used CustomerInternalID)queryId = query ID from a Query Builder (if you use multiple queries, use the comma separator) - more information in the Doxee Query Builder sectionprocessName = the location of the process (the process name will be provided either by your process designer or by Doxee)templateName = name of the template that will be used (optional)

Example: 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Make sure that the parameter names are spelled correctly, otherwise, the application won’t work. 

The URL can also be found in BTP - Cloud Foundry - Spaces - Subaccount - Approunter - Application Routes.

Make ‘Mashup Name’ descriptive as you will use it for assigning the mashup to a tab.The process must be saved in the Doxee repository in the folder Root -&gt; Processes

- Press ‘Save’.

#### When you are using Cloud development for SAP Sales and Service cloud service.
- Open the SAP Cloud Applications Studio. 

You can order SAP Cloud Application Studio in the SAP Software Center. [https://me.sap.com/softwarecenter](https://me.sap.com/softwarecenter)

- You need to login with your SAP Cloud Application Studio User. 

If you don’t have an SAP Cloud Application Studio user yet, you need to create it in the Sales Cloud. This is not the Administrator and the user requires special type of permissions. 

In the SAP Cloud Application Studio you can open the login window in Administrator → Log On. You might need to configure the System by clicking on the pencil icon next to it. In the Repository System Connections write the name and url of your Sales Cloud. 

- In the Project Explorer click on MashupConfiguration. &nbsp;![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

In case the Project Explorer is empty, you need to select the solution My Solutions tab.

&nbsp;

- To create a new Mashup right click on the MashupAuthoring. Chose the mashup type and you will be redirected to the Sales Cloud login page. Log in with your SAP Application Studio user. Now you will be redirected to the Administrator work center.

- Complete steps #4 &amp; #5 from the previous section.

## How to configure a Doxee app tab
- In the ‘User Menu’ click on ‘Start Adaptation’. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Navigate yourself to the page where you would like to configure the Doxee app (e.g.  Customers → Individual Customers → *click on customer itself*). Click on the edit button of the section of the page that you would like to edit. 

![A close-up of a screen  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- The edit mode will be displayed on the right side of the window. To add a new tab just click on the ‘Add’ button. 

![A screenshot of a application  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- The ‘Title’ of the tab is the name of the tab and it will be displayed on the portal page. The ‘Section Title’ is a subtitle that will be displayed when the tab is opened.

- Now you need to link the mashup to the newly created tab. Click on the edit button of the section by the tab name. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Again, on the right side of the window you will see the edit mode. 

- Here you can configure a new rule. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select a mashup from the table and click on ‘Apply’. Best practice is to select “Full Width” and Height 100%.

Make sure that you are in the ‘View’ mode. You might need to click few times on the back arrow in order to get there. Picture below.

![A screen shot of a phone  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)
